The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 New Nokia centre by year end

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Aug. 25: Nokia will set up a global network operations centre in India by the end of this year, said Simon Beresford-Wylie, executive vice-president and general manager, networks, at the companys Focus on India investor event here today.

 The centre will undertake network operations primarily for select operators in the Asia-Pacific region. It will also cater to Europe, West Asia and Africa as part of Nokias managed services offering. 

 The location of the site, which will initially employ up to 100 people, will be disclosed later. 




